did.abstract: Project files, minutes, correspondence, and property records, documenting the work of the New Haven Redevelopment Agency, primarily from the 1950s to the 1980s.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Deposited by the City of New Haven, 2003, 2005.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: New Haven Redevelopment Agency Records (MS 1814). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The New Haven Redevelopment Agency was established in 1950. It directed and oversaw the major redevelopment projects undertaken in New Haven from that time on.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Project files, minutes, correspondence, and property records, documenting the work of the New Haven Redevelopment Agency, primarily from the 1950s to the 1980s.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged in twenty-eight series and one addition: I. Administrative. II. Applications are Rehabilitation Loans. III. Capital Projects. IV. Chronological Files. V. City Housing Projects. VI. City of New Haven. VII. Contracts and Agreements. VIII. Demolition/Contracts. IX. Development Administrator's Files, 1980-1985. X. Environmental Impact. XI. Federal Government. XII. Housing Code Compliances. XIII. Litigation, Closed Files. XIV. Office of Land Disposition. XV. Office of Public Information. XVI. Open Space Program. XVII. Printed. XVIII. Projects. XIX. Regional Water Authority. XX. Reuse Parcel Survey Maps. XXI. State of Connecticut. XXII. Taft-Adams. XXIII. Urban Renewal in Other Cities. XXIV. Workable Programs. XXV. Card Files. XXVI. Minutes, 1959-1995. XXVII. Projects, Miscellaneous. XXVIII. Miscellaneous.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

Original audiovisual materials, as well as preservation and duplicating masters, may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy for their personal use should consult Copying Services information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.
